### Step 2: Update your MainActivity.java Code
Modify your `MainActivity.java` to add functionality for the button to increment a count whenever an item is added to the ArrayList:

```java
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.ArrayAdapter;
import android.widget.Button;
import android.widget.ListView;

import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;

import java.util.ArrayList;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {

    private ListView listView;
    private Button addButton;

    private ArrayList<String> stringList = new ArrayList<>();
    private int count = 0; // Count to track the number of added items

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);

        listView = findViewById(R.id.list_view);
        addButton = findViewById(R.id.add_button);

        // Set up the adapter
        final ArrayAdapter<String> adapter = new ArrayAdapter<>(this, android.R.layout.simple_list_item_1, stringList);
        listView.setAdapter(adapter);

        // Set Button onClickListener to add a new item
        addButton.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                count++; // Increment the count
                stringList.add("Item " + count); // Add new item with its count
                adapter.notifyDataSetChanged(); // Notify adapter of data change
            }
        });
    }
}
```

### Explanation
- **Count Variable**: A simple integer `count` is used to keep track of how many items have been added.
- **OnClickListener**: Whenever the button is clicked, the `count` is incremented, a new string using that count is added to the `stringList`, and the adapter is notified to refresh the ListView so that the new item appears.

### Result
Now, every time you click the "Add Item" button, the list will increase by one item with a label like "Item 1", "Item 2", etc., reflecting the incremented count dynamically.

